<div id="demo-region" class="container"></div>

<div class="container">
  <h2>Marionette Table Example</h2>
  <p class="lead">
    Our goal is to create a reusable, scalable dynamic table widget.
  </p>

  <p>
    We are dealing with users and their orders. Users can have many orders, but orders can only have one user.
  </p>


  <h4>Schema</h4>

  <p>(from db/schema.rb)</p>

  <pre class="pull-left">
  <code>
  create_table "orders", force: true do |t|
    t.integer  "user_id"
    t.decimal  "total"
    t.string   "notes"
    t.datetime "created_at"
    t.datetime "updated_at"
  end

  create_table "users", force: true do |t|
    t.string   "name"
    t.datetime "created_at"
    t.datetime "updated_at"
  end

  </code>
  </pre>


  <h4 style="clear:both">API</h4>

  <p>
    (output generated by <code>rake routes</code>)
  </p>

  <pre class="pull-left">
  <code>
       Prefix   Verb     URI Pattern            Controller#Action
  ---------------------------------------------------------------
   user_index   GET      /user(.:format)        user#index
  order_index   GET      /order(.:format)       order#index
                POST     /order(.:format)       order#create
        order   PATCH    /order/:id(.:format)   order#update
                PUT      /order/:id(.:format)   order#update
                DELETE   /order/:id(.:format)   order#destroy
  </code>
  </pre>
</div>

